Franklin, take his ass
back to school with you!

16:16.209 --> 16:19.879
-Make something of himself.
-LEON: At least if I shoot her,

16:19.912 --> 16:22.449
-they'll just put me
back inside, right?
-(chuckles)

16:22.482 --> 16:24.584
WANDA:
Leon, I'm not fucking
playing with you!

16:26.819 --> 16:28.455
Leon!

16:28.488 --> 16:30.457
Hey.

16:30.490 --> 16:33.060
Jerome still in that weed
and water game?

16:33.093 --> 16:35.095
Think he could put me on?

16:36.896 --> 16:38.698
I'll ask him.

16:38.731 --> 16:42.069
Franklin, there's six of us
in my mama's spot right now.

16:42.102 --> 16:44.504
I got to put something together.

16:47.274 --> 16:49.242
Hey, little nigga.

16:49.276 --> 16:51.311
With the fucking camera.

16:51.344 --> 16:53.413
-The fuck you doing?
-I'm filming.

16:53.446 --> 16:56.049
Yeah, I can see that.
What the fuck you doing it for?

16:56.083 --> 16:57.817
'Cause I'm making a movie.

16:57.850 --> 17:00.587
Nah, what you making is evidence
for the police.

17:00.620 --> 17:02.155
Let me see that shit.

17:02.189 --> 17:03.590
What? No!

17:03.623 --> 17:06.159
-Get off... get off me!
-Let go of the camera.

17:06.193 --> 17:08.995
-Give me that shit!
-Come on, man.

17:09.028 --> 17:10.997
-Let that man live.
-Ain't nobody in the hood

17:11.030 --> 17:13.400
making no motherfucking movie!

17:13.433 --> 17:15.635
With your square ass.

17:18.538 --> 17:20.540
Stupid-ass nigga.

17:23.743 --> 17:28.014
CISSY:
What happened at school
wasn't your fault, Franklin.

17:28.047 --> 17:31.050
And I'm not here
trying to punish you.

17:35.455 --> 17:37.857
It wouldn't hurt
to earn a few bucks

17:37.890 --> 17:41.128
while you're trying
to figure things out.

17:44.231 --> 17:46.933
I stopped by Cho's
on my way home.

17:46.966 --> 17:48.435
Said he's been sick.

17:48.468 --> 17:51.471
Could use some extra help.

17:56.943 --> 17:58.311
All right.

18:03.082 --> 18:07.954
* Tell me who you are... *

18:07.987 --> 18:09.456
JEROME:
Hey, Louie!

18:09.489 --> 18:11.458
* I want your love... *

18:11.491 --> 18:12.659
Sweetheart, why don't you
come over here

18:12.692 --> 18:14.093
and help us out with this shit?

18:14.127 --> 18:17.063
(laughs)
You seem to be doing just fine.

18:17.096 --> 18:19.466
(banging on door)

18:19.499 --> 18:20.633
JEROME:
Hold on, now.

18:22.001 --> 18:23.503
-Get the... get the dog.
-What should I do?

18:23.536 --> 18:25.238
Wait, wait, hold on. Hold on.

18:25.272 --> 18:27.140
FRANKLIN:
Wait, hold up.

18:27.174 --> 18:28.975
*

18:33.112 --> 18:34.614
(dog barking in distance)

18:34.647 --> 18:36.416
FRANKLIN:
Huh? I should get it?

18:36.449 --> 18:37.584
Yeah, get it, get it.

18:37.617 --> 18:39.686
Hey. Hold on, now, nephew.

18:39.719 --> 18:41.988
-(Jerome muttering)
-FRANKLIN: Wait. Hold up. Wait.

18:42.021 --> 18:44.824
(exhales) It's Leon.

18:44.857 --> 18:46.293
What's up, man?

18:46.326 --> 18:49.762
What the fuck
you so uptight for?

18:49.796 --> 18:51.598
Boy, you'll get
your goddamn ass shot.

18:51.631 --> 18:53.966
Who the fuck you gonna shoot
with that little-ass gun?

18:54.000 --> 18:55.134
(Jerome chuckling)

18:55.168 --> 18:56.936
You getting big, huh?

18:56.969 --> 18:59.506
Better way to get your ass shot.

18:59.539 --> 19:02.442
JEROME:
How much you want to start with?

19:02.475 --> 19:04.477
LEON:
I'll take a whole Z.

19:04.511 --> 19:06.279
JEROME:
That be 150.

19:06.313 --> 19:09.516
Now, I'm telling you right now,
don't make me into no asshole.

19:09.549 --> 19:12.285
You move it, you bring it back,
you set me right.

19:12.319 --> 19:14.554
I mean, I don't see
how that shit gonna stop you

19:14.587 --> 19:16.789
from being an asshole, but okay.

19:16.823 --> 19:18.891
JEROME:
Your boy got an attitude
problem, huh?

19:18.925 --> 19:20.727
LEON:
Shut the fuck up, nigga.
I'm right here.

19:20.760 --> 19:22.962
-Why the fuck you looking
at him? Huh?
-Come on, Lee.

19:22.995 --> 19:24.631
Come on, what?
This nigga already an asshole,

19:24.664 --> 19:26.466
been an asshole, gonna forever
be a fucking asshole.

19:26.499 --> 19:29.001
Huh?

19:29.035 --> 19:31.404
JEROME:
How about I slap the shit
out you with this pistol?

19:31.438 --> 19:34.173
-Go ahead. Slap me, nigga.
-Louie, shoot this motherfucker
in the head.

19:34.207 --> 19:36.175
-Get the fuck up, nigga.
-Little bitch-ass motherfucker.

19:36.209 --> 19:38.545
-Shut your ass up.
-You shut up.
I'll spray the fucking concrete

19:38.578 --> 19:40.747
-with your little bitch ass.
-Go ahead.
Who you shooting at, nigga?

19:40.780 --> 19:42.549
You ain't gonna shoot shit,
nigga.

19:42.582 --> 19:44.384
-You ain't never shot shit...
-Let me see your paperwork.

19:44.417 --> 19:46.553
Heard they was fucking your ass
up in goddamn county. Yeah!

19:54.193 --> 19:56.863
LEON:
I ain't even mind them
motherfuckers inside.

19:56.896 --> 19:58.598
Or the food.

19:58.631 --> 20:00.433
But the man got you
on his schedule

20:00.467 --> 20:02.335
every second of every day.

20:02.369 --> 20:05.137
And the guards treating you
like they own you.

20:06.239 --> 20:08.140
Shit wear on you.

20:10.109 --> 20:12.078
Everybody's owned by somebody.

20:12.111 --> 20:14.046
(kids chattering playfully)

20:14.080 --> 20:15.582
Not like this.

20:17.284 --> 20:20.186
Hey, why the fuck
you ain't at that school?

20:20.219 --> 20:23.923
Thought for sure
you wasn't ever coming back.

20:23.956 --> 20:25.958
(clicks tongue)
I got fucked.

20:27.594 --> 20:31.030
(sighs)
Maybe I fucked myself.

20:31.063 --> 20:33.032
I don't know.

20:33.065 --> 20:35.768
Thought I could play their game
my way and still win.

20:35.802 --> 20:37.203
(chuckles)

20:37.236 --> 20:39.205
Franklin Saint.

20:39.238 --> 20:41.641
Always thinking
there's a better way.

20:44.277 --> 20:46.679
So, what's the better way now?

21:07.266 --> 21:10.102
Franklin Saint?

21:11.538 --> 21:12.939
(car door closes)

21:12.972 --> 21:15.107
Hey, I'm Teddy McDonald.

21:15.141 --> 21:18.678
Y-You came to a presentation
I gave at Claremont.

21:23.115 --> 21:25.585
You're the recruiter?

21:25.618 --> 21:26.986
Yeah.
(chuckles)

21:27.019 --> 21:28.621
Sorry to just show up like this.
(clears throat)

21:28.655 --> 21:30.957
I was wondering if maybe
you had a few minutes to talk.

21:40.132 --> 21:42.402
Great.

21:44.871 --> 21:46.773
It's just you and your mom?

21:46.806 --> 21:49.376
Uh-huh.

21:50.643 --> 21:53.446
-Your dad?
-Uh...

21:53.480 --> 21:56.349
He'd been living
on the streets a long time.

21:56.383 --> 21:59.386
Cops gave him a beating a few
years back. He didn't make it.

22:04.691 --> 22:06.659
-I'm sorry to hear that.
-Look, I don't mean to be rude,

22:06.693 --> 22:09.061
-but, uh, what...
-What the hell am I doing here?

22:09.095 --> 22:10.697
(chuckles):
Yeah, yeah.

22:10.730 --> 22:12.665
(chuckles)

22:12.699 --> 22:14.300
I came to see if the CIA

22:14.333 --> 22:16.268
might be the right career path
for you.

22:17.937 --> 22:19.539
I'm sorry, what?
(chuckles)

22:19.572 --> 22:23.042
The... the CIA?

22:24.276 --> 22:26.746
You came here to hire me?

22:26.779 --> 22:30.883
Well, um, I mean, you'd have to
finish school first, of course.

22:30.917 --> 22:33.019
And then you would go
through our process.

22:33.052 --> 22:36.489
Exams, interviews, background
checks, there's a polygraph.

22:36.523 --> 22:38.290
You know, it's not easy, but...

22:39.358 --> 22:41.761
...from what I hear,
you can handle it.

22:42.795 --> 22:44.864
And what did you hear?

22:44.897 --> 22:48.435
3.9 GPA, double major

22:48.468 --> 22:51.170
political science, economics.

22:51.203 --> 22:52.739
1540 on your SATs.

22:52.772 --> 22:55.942
Your professors speak glowingly
about your work ethic

22:55.975 --> 22:58.277
and your critical thinking.

22:58.310 --> 23:01.581
And you've shown
an acute ability to move easily

23:01.614 --> 23:03.249
between worlds.

23:03.282 --> 23:06.686
I should add that diversity
has become

23:06.719 --> 23:08.755
increasingly important
to the Agency.

23:08.788 --> 23:11.858
You see, to meet
ever more complex goals

23:11.891 --> 23:14.494
going forward, we have
to broaden our perspectives.

23:15.562 --> 23:17.296
You seem surprised.

23:17.329 --> 23:21.200
(chuckles)
I just never thought about

23:21.233 --> 23:23.903
-working for the government.
-Really?

23:26.606 --> 23:30.276
D-Do you mind if I ask why?

23:30.309 --> 23:33.713
You know, the... the government
never cared about me.

23:33.746 --> 23:37.183
So, why help them?

23:39.285 --> 23:41.488
This kind of work's
not for everyone.

23:45.157 --> 23:47.760
Why do you do it?

23:47.794 --> 23:49.428
-Tradition.
-Mm.

23:49.462 --> 23:52.131
Duty.

23:52.164 --> 23:56.736
And I believe in America.
Its mission.

23:56.769 --> 24:00.840
You know, they recruited me
at Yale, 'cause, uh,

24:00.873 --> 24:02.975
I was the best
and the brightest.

24:03.009 --> 24:05.578
Like you.

24:05.612 --> 24:08.748
Well, you know,
e-even if I was interested,

24:08.781 --> 24:11.017
there's a problem...

24:11.050 --> 24:13.986
with school.

24:14.020 --> 24:16.489
A problem like you assaulting
the financial aid officer?

24:19.458 --> 24:21.360
Rumor has it
that Alexander Hamilton punched

24:21.393 --> 24:24.631
-a bursar at Princeton.
-(chuckling): For real?

24:24.664 --> 24:26.365
Man. Wow.

24:26.398 --> 24:28.735
You know, we're not looking
for spotless backgrounds.

24:29.802 --> 24:32.471
We're looking for people
with backbones.

24:32.505 --> 24:36.442
And if you're concerned
about getting back into school,

24:36.475 --> 24:39.311
consider that taken care of.

24:39.345 --> 24:43.883
Anyway, uh, I'm gonna be in L.A.
for a few more weeks,

24:43.916 --> 24:45.284
but then I'm gonna be
back in D.C.

24:45.317 --> 24:47.787
After that, uh,
if you're interested,

24:47.820 --> 24:49.689
give this number a call.
They'll put us in touch.

24:49.722 --> 24:51.691
Theodore McDonald.
(chuckles)

25:01.868 --> 25:03.570
-Have a good one.
-Yeah.

25:03.603 --> 25:05.672
-You be safe out there.
-Sure thing.

25:12.679 --> 25:14.681
(indistinct voices on radio)

25:16.849 --> 25:18.517
Thank you.

25:23.189 --> 25:26.492
Oh, my bad.
Go right ahead.

25:26.525 --> 25:28.027
(chuckles)

25:28.060 --> 25:30.229
Cute-ass couple.

25:32.264 --> 25:35.602
-What's going on, little homey?
-What's up, man?

25:35.635 --> 25:36.936
Ain't nothing.

25:36.969 --> 25:40.873
Let me, uh, get
this box of Apple Smacks

25:40.907 --> 25:45.044
and, uh... oh, shit,
them yellow flip-flops.

25:45.077 --> 25:47.246
-Yeah, let me get a pair.
-All right, man.

25:47.279 --> 25:49.548
-Hey, size 13.
-(exhales)

25:49.582 --> 25:51.250
We ain't got no 13s.

25:51.283 --> 25:54.587
Damn, that's all good.
Hey, check this out, though.

25:54.621 --> 25:56.555
I guess I'll take all the money
in the register.

25:56.589 --> 25:59.191
Let's go, nigga. This your
first time being robbed?

25:59.225 --> 26:01.728
-Move! Get that money.
-(cash register rings)

26:01.761 --> 26:04.463
Let's go, man,
hurry your ass up!

26:04.496 --> 26:06.532
Nervous nigga
knocking shit down.

26:06.565 --> 26:10.036
Man, hell nah, this ain't
all you got. Go back, man.

26:10.069 --> 26:11.537
Take all the money out.

26:11.570 --> 26:14.641
Hell wrong with you, man?
Shit.

26:14.674 --> 26:18.444
Do with these coins, nigga?
I ain't riding the bus.

26:18.477 --> 26:20.713
Matter of fact, run that money
in your pocket, too.

26:20.747 --> 26:23.650
Shit. Let's go, nigga!

26:23.683 --> 26:24.951
Shit.

26:24.984 --> 26:27.486
Two dollars?

26:27.519 --> 26:28.988
Shit. Broke-ass nigga, man.

26:29.021 --> 26:31.557
Man, just-just take it and go.

26:31.590 --> 26:33.092
The fuck you say to me?

26:33.125 --> 26:36.395
-What, you trying
to tell me what to do?
-No.

26:36.428 --> 26:39.231
-Oh, you think
you're my boss, huh?
-No.

26:39.265 --> 26:41.734
-No.
-Nigga, you ain't shit.

26:41.768 --> 26:44.170
I'll take your fucking life
right now if I want to.

26:44.203 --> 26:46.605
Matter of fact.

26:46.639 --> 26:48.941
Hey, say you're my bitch.

26:48.975 --> 26:50.677
What?

26:50.710 --> 26:51.944
Say it, nigga,
right fucking now!

26:51.978 --> 26:53.545
I'm-I'm your bitch.

26:54.446 --> 26:56.448
(Franklin panting)

26:57.717 --> 27:00.653
Now say you're my fucking bitch.

27:00.687 --> 27:02.454
I'm your bitch, man.

27:02.488 --> 27:04.256
I'm your bitch.

27:04.290 --> 27:06.192
Trying to lose
your goddamn life tonight?

27:06.225 --> 27:08.761
-Ass end up on the news, nigga.
-(door opens)

27:08.795 --> 27:09.996
Fuck wrong with you?

27:13.332 --> 27:14.867
ANDRE:
No, no, no, no, no!

27:17.636 --> 27:20.572
*

27:45.064 --> 27:48.034
(indistinct voices on radio)

27:48.067 --> 27:50.069
You all right, Franklin?

27:54.941 --> 27:56.909
(breathing shakily)

27:56.943 --> 27:58.911
ANDRE:
Officer needs help.

27:58.945 --> 28:00.346
Shots fired.

28:00.379 --> 28:02.681
Cho's market.

28:02.715 --> 28:05.217
Requesting ambulance and backup.

28:05.251 --> 28:06.919
Black male.

28:06.953 --> 28:08.420
Not responding.

28:08.454 --> 28:09.722
Not breathing.

28:09.756 --> 28:11.724
WOMAN (over radio):
10-4. Confirm Cho's market.

28:11.758 --> 28:13.760
Backup and rescue unit
on the way.

28:21.400 --> 28:22.869
-Came in through the door.
-Okay.

28:22.902 --> 28:25.671
Saw the suspect
with the gun in his hand.

28:25.704 --> 28:26.739
He fired a shot at me.

28:26.773 --> 28:29.708
I ducked, fired three shots...

28:43.722 --> 28:45.524
-Excuse us.
-CISSY: Franklin?

28:45.557 --> 28:47.293
-Ma'am.
-Sorry.

28:47.326 --> 28:48.694
-Ma-Ma'am.
-Franklin.

28:48.727 --> 28:50.729
Oh, my God.

28:53.732 --> 28:56.102
-Are you okay?
-Mm-hmm.

28:56.135 --> 28:59.105
God. Come on.

28:59.138 --> 29:01.140
Let's get you out of here.

29:03.342 --> 29:05.344
FRANKLIN:
Thank you.

29:19.325 --> 29:21.060
CISSY:
That's it.

29:21.093 --> 29:22.995
You're going back
to school somewhere.

29:23.029 --> 29:25.031
I will find the money.

29:26.833 --> 29:30.002
FRANKLIN:
I'm not going back
to that world.

29:31.037 --> 29:33.739
I don't belong there.

29:33.772 --> 29:36.775
You don't belong here,
either, Franklin.

29:39.778 --> 29:41.780
You're too big for this place.

29:44.783 --> 29:46.953
FRANKLIN:
I don't know what to do, Mama.

29:55.962 --> 29:58.730
CISSY:
You know, I've had
this conversation before.

29:59.798 --> 30:01.968
With your father.

30:03.970 --> 30:06.772
He felt the same way.

30:06.805 --> 30:10.943
Betrayed by the Panthers,
by his country.

30:10.977 --> 30:14.046
A man without a place
in this world.

30:18.350 --> 30:20.319
But he let them win.

30:22.188 --> 30:24.123
He gave up.

30:24.156 --> 30:26.959
Mm-mm.

30:26.993 --> 30:29.195
You don't have to know how,

30:29.228 --> 30:31.163
but you have to keep going.

30:31.197 --> 30:32.798
You can do anything you want.

30:32.831 --> 30:34.800
Reapply for a scholarship

30:34.833 --> 30:36.802
to an all-black college
and finish school.

30:36.835 --> 30:38.670
Or go back to that...

30:38.704 --> 30:39.705
You have to keep going...

30:39.738 --> 30:41.540
And refuse to leave

30:41.573 --> 30:42.641
until they give you a job.

30:42.674 --> 30:43.876
You can do anything you want...

30:43.910 --> 30:46.879
Use them to learn the system,
pass the exams...

30:46.913 --> 30:48.414
You have to keep going...

30:48.447 --> 30:49.715
...and then come back
to South Central

30:49.748 --> 30:50.716
and open your own firm.

30:50.749 --> 30:52.351
You can do anything you want.

30:52.384 --> 30:54.987
Your ancestors suffered horrors

30:55.021 --> 30:57.756
beyond imagining
to give you this opportunity.

30:57.789 --> 30:59.091
You have to keep going...

30:59.125 --> 31:00.692
I've done all I can.
You can do anything you want.

31:00.726 --> 31:03.095
There is grace
for those who seek it.

31:03.129 --> 31:05.597
I believe it in my heart.

31:05.631 --> 31:08.534
You will be all right,
Franklin.

31:08.567 --> 31:12.871
But you have to stay and fight.

31:24.550 --> 31:26.552
(panting)

