35:29.461 --> 35:34.800
Your, uh, dad and I
are gonna step out for a bit.

35:34.833 --> 35:37.669
Okay?

35:38.904 --> 35:42.541
-Need anything?
-Nah, I'm good.

35:44.643 --> 35:46.011
All right.

36:04.496 --> 36:06.932
Thank you for coming.

36:11.603 --> 36:13.405
We in trouble.

36:13.439 --> 36:17.142
Okay? Drifting. Profits is down.

36:17.175 --> 36:19.144
Violence is rising.
The gangs at war.

36:19.177 --> 36:23.048
This entire business is about
to spin out of control...

36:23.081 --> 36:26.051
No.

36:26.084 --> 36:28.587
-JEROME: Cissy...
-He is not ready.

36:28.620 --> 36:30.689
LOUIE:
You need to let him
make that choice.

36:30.722 --> 36:32.658
(scoffs)
I most certainly do not.

36:32.691 --> 36:35.193
He started this shit.

36:37.529 --> 36:39.498
And it almost killed him.

36:39.531 --> 36:41.600
Three minutes
he was on that table.

36:41.633 --> 36:43.835
-His heart stopped.
-I was there. We all was there.

36:43.869 --> 36:46.872
Then how dare you ask me
to push him back in?

36:55.213 --> 36:59.084
If he ever does come back,
it'll be when we...

36:59.117 --> 37:01.753
-Oh, get the fuck out of here.
-...decide that he's able.

37:01.787 --> 37:03.789
-Decide what?
-And if y'all can't manage
this shit without him...

37:03.822 --> 37:05.357
Then what?

37:05.391 --> 37:07.759
Then you should have
the good sense to walk away

37:07.793 --> 37:10.862
before somebody else dies
up in this piece.

37:10.896 --> 37:13.799
-Woman, you know you're in the
goddamn drug game now, right?
-LOUIE: You know that?

37:13.832 --> 37:16.402
-Do you know that?
-Why don't you go have
a fucking kid before you got...

37:16.435 --> 37:18.804
Oh, shut the fuck up with the
goddamn kid shit! You don't make

37:18.837 --> 37:21.139
-no fucking decisions...
-You don't motherfucking get
to make this decision!

37:21.172 --> 37:23.909
-You know you're a fucking
drug dealer now, right?
-He's my motherfucking son!

37:23.942 --> 37:26.712
-This is my shit!
-I don't give a fuck
what you say!

37:26.745 --> 37:28.447
-CISSY: That's my goddamn son!
-ALTON: This is my wife, Jerome.

37:28.480 --> 37:30.949
-You understand me?
-Franklin!

37:32.784 --> 37:35.854
Fucking hardheaded.

37:42.260 --> 37:45.063
It's okay, Mama.

37:45.096 --> 37:47.265
Huh?

37:49.134 --> 37:52.037
All right. I'm here.

37:54.306 --> 37:56.975
Talk to me.

37:57.008 --> 37:59.811
CISSY:
I still don't understand why.

37:59.845 --> 38:03.615
We have the money, we can leave.

38:03.649 --> 38:05.250
All of us.

38:05.283 --> 38:07.285
Start a life somewhere else.

38:09.321 --> 38:11.990
I didn't build all of this
just to make a bunch of money

38:12.023 --> 38:14.826
and leave, abandon our people.

38:14.860 --> 38:17.262
You telling me this is still
about our people?

38:17.295 --> 38:19.431
Have you taken a look about
what's going on out there?

38:19.465 --> 38:22.434
I have. And that's exactly why
I can't leave now.

38:22.468 --> 38:23.935
ALTON:
You can't control what happens,

38:23.969 --> 38:25.471
Franklin.

38:25.504 --> 38:28.173
-You can't stop what's coming.
-Maybe, maybe not.

38:28.206 --> 38:33.845
But what I know for sure is,
if we bail,

38:33.879 --> 38:36.815
there'll be chaos.

38:36.848 --> 38:40.151
We'll leave a vacuum, for sure.

38:40.185 --> 38:44.856
Gangs battling over control
and territory.

38:44.890 --> 38:47.459
And an entire fucking community
in ruins.

38:47.493 --> 38:49.227
Is that what you want?

38:49.260 --> 38:51.329
You still haven't fully healed.

38:51.363 --> 38:53.365
(exhales)

39:02.608 --> 39:05.076
(ragged exhale)

39:06.344 --> 39:07.913
I've healed enough.

39:08.947 --> 39:12.684
And I have to stay and fight.

39:12.718 --> 39:14.720
I'm sorry.

39:21.927 --> 39:24.530
I got to...

39:24.563 --> 39:28.033
got to go take care
of something.

39:30.068 --> 39:32.070
I love you.

39:51.289 --> 39:53.291
(engine shuts off)

39:57.463 --> 39:59.431
Ah.

39:59.465 --> 40:02.133
You are a sight for sore eyes.
(chuckles)

40:02.167 --> 40:04.369
Ain't I glad to see you.

40:04.402 --> 40:07.739
(train horn blows)

40:07.773 --> 40:10.375
-You look good.
-Ah.

40:10.408 --> 40:12.744
Look like I'm hurting,
which I am.

40:16.181 --> 40:17.983
But I've subscribed
to the notion

40:18.016 --> 40:20.986
that whatever doesn't kill us
simply makes us...

40:22.287 --> 40:24.890
-Stronger.
-Sharper.

40:24.923 --> 40:26.492
Sharper.

40:28.293 --> 40:31.362
Did you know that L.A. used
to suffer from serious floods?

40:33.532 --> 40:36.267
TEDDY:
Yeah, I think I heard that
at some point.

40:36.301 --> 40:37.903
FRANKLIN:
You know,
they tried building dams,

40:37.936 --> 40:39.938
but that didn't solve it.

40:39.971 --> 40:43.408
So after a couple disastrous
floods in the '30s,

40:43.441 --> 40:46.478
L.A. reached out
to the federal government.

40:47.713 --> 40:49.848
And they brought in
the Army Corps of Engineers,

40:49.881 --> 40:53.685
and in 20 years they built
and designed the L.A. River,

40:53.719 --> 40:58.156
a 50-mile waterway that saved
the City of Angels.

41:04.229 --> 41:07.633
I was right about this rock.

41:07.666 --> 41:11.637
We're making more money than
we ever could've dreamed of.

41:11.670 --> 41:15.641
What I was wrong about
was the cost.

41:16.675 --> 41:19.645
Lives are gonna be destroyed.

41:19.678 --> 41:23.782
Ain't a thing I can do about
that now except to keep going,

41:23.815 --> 41:27.218
keep things under control
as best I can, you know?

41:31.022 --> 41:33.424
Yeah, how do you do that?

41:36.194 --> 41:38.396
I bring in
the federal government.

41:40.265 --> 41:44.069
I'll identify anybody
who poses a threat to stability,

41:44.102 --> 41:46.972
and you'll help me
take 'em down.

41:47.005 --> 41:50.208
That's how we keep
the violence at bay,

41:50.241 --> 41:53.211
stay out the papers
so we can make that paper. Huh?

41:53.244 --> 41:54.846
(chuckles)

41:54.880 --> 41:57.583
Why would I help you do that?

41:57.616 --> 41:59.250
Well, because...

42:01.753 --> 42:05.456
...the CIA wants me to keep
flowing money here, Reed.

42:08.694 --> 42:14.032
Or James Smith or Thomas Parker
or whatever your name is.

42:16.467 --> 42:19.170
You can destroy me any time
you want, I get it.

42:19.204 --> 42:24.442
But you see, the thing is,
I'm not afraid of dying anymore.

42:25.644 --> 42:28.413
Not even so much afraid
of prison.

42:28.446 --> 42:31.416
But what I will not be

42:31.449 --> 42:35.186
is a slave... to anyone.

42:35.220 --> 42:37.222
Even you.

42:41.092 --> 42:43.629
Remember McDonald's?

42:43.662 --> 42:45.463
Thousand keys a week?

42:45.496 --> 42:47.532
Oh, yeah.

42:47.565 --> 42:49.134
I'll make you
so much fucking money,

42:49.167 --> 42:51.536
you'll be able to fund that war
all by yourself.

42:51.569 --> 42:55.040
They're gonna name a wing at the
CIA headquarters after your ass.

42:55.073 --> 42:57.643
Real American hero shit.

42:57.676 --> 43:01.246
And in return, you'll make sure
that me and mine are protected.

43:01.279 --> 43:03.414
And at the end of this,
the both of us

43:03.448 --> 43:06.317
are gonna ride off
into the sunset.

43:06.351 --> 43:08.353
("Law of the Land"
by The Temptations playing)

43:11.422 --> 43:14.259
You said you'd be here with me
until the end.

43:21.867 --> 43:24.302
Did you really mean it?

43:30.976 --> 43:35.246
* Some people
will always have it made *

43:35.280 --> 43:37.248
* Some people will live
in poverty *

43:37.282 --> 43:39.250
* For the rest of their days *

43:39.284 --> 43:43.989
* Time marches on *

43:44.022 --> 43:47.158
* Yesterday is dead and gone *

43:47.192 --> 43:50.328
* Life is uncertain *

43:50.361 --> 43:51.863
-* Let me hear you say *
-* Yeah *

43:51.897 --> 43:55.033
* Death is final, yes, it is *

43:56.634 --> 43:59.671
* There'll be days
of sunshine and laughter *

43:59.705 --> 44:04.309
* But don't forget you're gonna
have to shed some tears *

44:04.342 --> 44:05.844
* Whoa-ho *

44:05.877 --> 44:08.947
* It's the law of the land,
my brother *

44:08.980 --> 44:12.017
* Oh, whether you like it
or you understand *

44:12.050 --> 44:13.618
* Ah, hey-hey *

44:13.651 --> 44:15.120
* It's the law of the land *

44:15.153 --> 44:18.223
* Hey, hey, hey, hey *

44:18.256 --> 44:21.727
* Laws made by almighty man *

44:21.760 --> 44:23.328
* Live by the good book. *

